00057 static Key *rna_ShapeKey_find_key(ID *id)
00058 {
00059     switch (GS(id->name)) {
00060         case ID_CU: return ((Curve*)id)->key;
00061         case ID_KE: return (Key*)id;
00062         case ID_LT: return ((Lattice*)id)->key;
00063         case ID_ME: return ((Mesh*)id)->key;
00064         case ID_OB: return ob_get_key((Object*)id);
00065         default: return NULL;
00066     }
00067 }

00069 void rna_ShapeKey_name_set(PointerRNA *ptr, const char *value)
00070 {
00071     KeyBlock *kb = ptr->data;
00072     char oldname[sizeof(kb->name)];
00073     
00074     /* make a copy of the old name first */
00075     BLI_strncpy(oldname, kb->name, sizeof(kb->name));
00076     
00077     /* copy the new name into the name slot */
00078     BLI_strncpy_utf8(kb->name, value, sizeof(kb->name));
00079     
00080     /* make sure the name is truly unique */
00081     if (ptr->id.data) {
00082         Key *key = rna_ShapeKey_find_key(ptr->id.data);
00083         BLI_uniquename(&key->block, kb, "Key", '.', offsetof(KeyBlock, name), sizeof(kb->name));
00084     }
00085     
00086     /* fix all the animation data which may link to this */
00087     BKE_all_animdata_fix_paths_rename(NULL, "key_blocks", oldname, kb->name);
00088 }

00284 static void rna_ShapeKey_data_begin(CollectionPropertyIterator *iter, PointerRNA *ptr)
00285 {
00286     Key *key = rna_ShapeKey_find_key(ptr->id.data);
00287     KeyBlock *kb = (KeyBlock*)ptr->data;
00288     Curve *cu;
00289     Nurb *nu;
00290     int tot = kb->totelem, size = key->elemsize;
00291     
00292     if (GS(key->from->name) == ID_CU) {
00293         cu = (Curve*)key->from;
00294         nu = cu->nurb.first;
00295         
00296         if (nu->bezt) {
00297             tot /= 3;
00298             size *= 3;
00299         }
00300     }
00301     
00302     rna_iterator_array_begin(iter, (void*)kb->data, size, tot, 0, NULL);
00303 }

00324 static PointerRNA rna_ShapeKey_data_get(CollectionPropertyIterator *iter)
00325 {
00326     Key *key = rna_ShapeKey_find_key(iter->parent.id.data);
00327     StructRNA *type;
00328     Curve *cu;
00329     Nurb *nu;
00330     
00331     if (GS(key->from->name) == ID_CU) {
00332         cu = (Curve*)key->from;
00333         nu = cu->nurb.first;
00334         
00335         if (nu->bezt)
00336             type = &RNA_ShapeKeyBezierPoint;
00337         else
00338             type = &RNA_ShapeKeyCurvePoint;
00339     }
00340     else
00341         type = &RNA_ShapeKeyPoint;
00342     
00343     return rna_pointer_inherit_refine(&iter->parent, type, rna_iterator_array_get(iter));
00344 }

00370 static KeyBlock *rna_ShapeKeyData_find_keyblock(Key *key, float *point)
00371 {
00372     KeyBlock *kb;
00373     
00374     /* sanity checks */
00375     if (ELEM(NULL, key, point))
00376         return NULL;
00377     
00378     /* we'll need to manually search through the keyblocks and check
00379      * if the point is somewhere in the middle of each block's data
00380      */
00381     for (kb = key->block.first; kb; kb = kb->next) {
00382         if (kb->data) {
00383             float *start = (float *)kb->data;
00384             float *end;
00385             
00386             /* easy cases first */
00387             if ((start == NULL) || (start > point)) {
00388                 /* there's no chance point is in array */
00389                 continue;
00390             }
00391             else if (start == point) {
00392                 /* exact match - point is first in array */
00393                 return kb;
00394             }
00395             
00396             /* determine where end of array is
00397              *  - elemsize is in bytes, so use char* cast to get array in terms of bytes
00398              */
00399             end = (float *)((char *)start + (key->elemsize * kb->totelem));
00400             
00401             /* if point's address is less than the end, then it is somewhere between start and end, so in array */
00402             if (end > point) {
00403                 /* we've found the owner of the point data */
00404                 return kb;
00405             }
00406         }
00407     }
00408     
00409     return NULL;
00410 }

00412 static int rna_ShapeKeyPoint_get_index(Key *key, KeyBlock *kb, float *point)
00413 {
00414     /* if we frame the data array and point pointers as char*, then the difference between
00415      * them will be in bytes. Thus, dividing through by key->elemsize (number of bytes per point)
00416      * gives us the offset of point from start of array.
00417      */
00418     char *start = (char *)kb->data;
00419     char *pt = (char *)point;
00420     
00421     return (int)(pt - start) / key->elemsize;
00422 }

00424 static char *rna_ShapeKeyPoint_path(PointerRNA *ptr)
00425 {
00426     ID *id = (ID *)ptr->id.data;
00427     Key *key = rna_ShapeKey_find_key(ptr->id.data);
00428     KeyBlock *kb;
00429     float *point = (float *)ptr->data;
00430     
00431     /* if we can get a key block, we can construct a path */
00432     kb = rna_ShapeKeyData_find_keyblock(key, point);
00433     
00434     if (kb) {
00435         int index = rna_ShapeKeyPoint_get_index(key, kb, point);
00436         
00437         if (GS(id->name) == ID_KE)
00438             return BLI_sprintfN("key_blocks[\"%s\"].data[%d]", kb->name, index);
00439         else
00440             return BLI_sprintfN("shape_keys.key_blocks[\"%s\"].data[%d]", kb->name, index);
00441     }
00442     else
00443         return NULL; /* XXX: there's really no way to resolve this... */
00444 }
